# Git Commit Conventions

Clean, incremental history for the beecrowd/Winter assessment: **one feature branch**
for all implementation, **commits per phase** — no branch changes between phases.

## Branch model

| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `master` | Planning: specs, constitution, tasks, `.cursor/rules/`, README workflow |
| `001-ai-order-engine` | All implementation T001–T052 (every phase on this branch) |

- Branch name matches feature directory: `specs/001-ai-order-engine` → `001-ai-order-engine`.
- **Do not** create a branch per phase or user story.
- **Do not** commit implementation code (`src/`, `prisma/`, `tests/`, Docker) on `master`.
- Governance (`.cursor/rules/`, spec templates) commits go on `master` only.
- When the feature is done: open PR `001-ai-order-engine` → `master`.

Spec-kit resolves tasks via `.specify/feature.json`, not git branch name.

## Commits per phase (same branch throughout)

Never squash the full implementation into one commit. Commit after each **checkpoint**
in `specs/001-ai-order-engine/tasks.md`.

- Commit only when the user explicitly asks (e.g. "commit T010-T011").
- After a checkpoint, suggest a commit — stay on `001-ai-order-engine`, do not switch branches.
- One logical unit per commit: setup slice, schema, tests, service, routes, or docs.
- Do NOT commit unrelated phases together (e.g. orders API + AI chat in one commit).

## Message format (Conventional Commits)

```text
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary ≤72 chars>

Refs: T0XX[-T0YY]
```

**Types**: `feat` | `test` | `chore` | `docs` | `fix` | `refactor`

**Language**: English for commit subjects.

## Suggested commit map

| Phase | Suggested commits | Tasks |
|-------|-------------------|-------|
| Setup | scaffold + deps; docker compose; assets + layout | T001-T009 |
| Foundational | prisma schema + migration; lib clients + lock; services skeleton + tests | T010-T019 |
| US1 | order tests; order service; order API routes | T020-T026 |
| US2 | cancel tests; cancel service + route | T027-T030 |
| US3 | batch tests; batch service + cron; trigger route + logging | T031-T037 |
| US4 | chat tool tests; KB + tools + agent; chat API + UI | T038-T045 |
| Polish | swagger asset; README SDD + GenAI; validation fixes | T046-T052 |

Prefer **test commit before feat** when TDD applies (e.g. T020 before T022).

## Workflow

```text
master                    → planning & governance
  └── 001-ai-order-engine → all phases, commits only (no branch switches)
        ├── commit Phase 1 Setup
        ├── commit Phase 2 Foundational
        ├── commit US1 … US4
        └── PR → master
```

## Files to NEVER commit

`.env`, secrets, `node_modules/`, `.next/`, local IDE config with credentials.

## After committing

Run `git status` — working tree clean before starting the next phase.
